id: pm-lwps
title: Add governance batch-mutation mode with explicit ownership override planning
description: "Provide a safe orchestration mode for governance operations that precomputes required ownership overrides, surfaces approval-ready plans, and executes deterministic batches with per-item audit traces."
type: Feature
status: in_progress
priority: 2
tags[4]: automation,governance,ownership,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-04-04T21:55:27.146Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-05T21:14:11.811Z"
deadline: "2026-04-25T21:55:27.146Z"
assignee: codex-agent
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 300
acceptance_criteria: "A governance batch mode can generate an override plan (dry-run), list affected assignees/items, require explicit confirmation, and execute scoped mutations with clear per-item audit output."
definition_of_ready: Ownership conflict patterns from governance sweeps are documented and acceptance safety constraints are defined.
goal: Governance operations by default
objective: Reduce manual ownership-conflict remediation during approved audits
value: Lowers execution friction for legitimate cross-owner governance maintenance
impact: Cuts repetitive force operations while preserving transparent safety controls
outcome: Approved governance runs can execute at scale with clear auditability
why_now: The latest standards-alignment run required over 200 ownership override updates handled manually.
parent: pm-5rjn
reviewer: maintainer-review
risk: high
confidence: medium
sprint: governance-followups
release: vnext
reporter: codex-agent
severity: medium
environment: linux
repro_steps: Run large governance normalization over cross-owned items and observe repetitive ownership conflict handling.
affected_version: 2026.3.12
component: governance-batch-ownership
regression: false
customer_impact: Maintainers can execute approved governance maintenance faster with explicit safety evidence.
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-04T21:55:27.146Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: pm search 'ownership conflict force audit override workflow' --limit 20; pm search 'ownership-safe batch mutation mode governance override' --limit 20; pm list-open --limit 20. Net-new because current items improve guidance only; no feature currently provides plan+execute batch ownership override workflow for governance operations."
  "2026-04-05T20:39:58.011Z",codex-agent,Duplicate-check evidence refreshed; existing open feature reused as canonical parent for transactional annotate/batch mutation implementation (no duplicate item created).
  "2026-04-05T21:14:11.811Z",codex-agent,"Progress: implemented transactional update surface for metadata + comments/notes/learnings/files/tests/docs using additive --comment/--note/--learning/--file/--test/--doc flags on pm update, with explicit none-clearing semantics and single-mutation changed_fields tracking. Verification: pnpm vitest tests/unit/update-command.spec.ts tests/unit/completion-command.spec.ts tests/unit/pi-agent-extension.spec.ts passed; pnpm build passed; pnpm vitest tests/integration/cli.integration.spec.ts -t 'supports transactional update mutations for linked files/docs/tests and log collections' passed; pnpm vitest tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts -t 'keeps update help aligned with required flags and aliases' passed."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-04T21:55:27.146Z",codex-agent,Design should separate planning and execution phases and require explicit operator confirmation before any forced mutation batch.
